OL,3,COver-the-counter nasal sprays may keep
OL,4,Ccoughs, colds and flu at bay, trial
OL,5,Cshows
OL,7,FUsing nasal sprays at the first sign
OL,8,Fof a sore throat, cough, cold or flu
OL,9,Fcould stop full-blown symptoms from
OL,10,Fdeveloping and help speed up recovery,
OL,11,Faccording to the largest trial of its
OL,12,Fkind.
OL,14,FData from nearly 14,000 adults has
OL,15,Fshown over-the-counter gel and saline
OL,16,Fsprays cut the number of days spent
OL,17,Ffeeling ill with sinus and chest
OL,18,Finfections, flu and cold by around 20%.
