OL,3,COver-the-counter nasal sprays may keep
OL,4,Ccoughs, colds and flu at bay, trial
OL,5,Cshows
OL,7,FPaul Little, professor in primary care
OL,8,Fresearch from the University of
OL,9,FSouthampton, who led the trial, said:
OL,10,F"Given these results, our advice,
OL,11,Fparticularly for those at higher risk
OL,12,Ffrom infections or those who get
OL,13,Frecurrent infections, is at the first
OL,14,Fsign of cough, sore throat, cold or
OL,15,Fflu-like symptoms, use a nasal spray
OL,16,Fto prevent it from developing fully,
OL,17,Fand to use the sprays preventatively
OL,18,Fafter close exposure to people with
OL,19,Finfections."
